n the western\nhemisphere. Combined scattered and thermal emitted light predictions are\nconsistent with published HST and Spitzer secondary transit observations. Our\nmodel predictions are also consistent with geometric albedo constraints from\noptical wavelength ground based polarimetry and HST B-band measurements. We\npredict an apparent geometric albedo for HD 189733b of 0.205 and 0.229, in the\nTESS and CHEOPS photometric bands respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Jan 2017 12:31:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 18 Jan 2017 11:48:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-04"}
